tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE StressData (
  user_id INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  stress_level INT,
  heart_rate INT,
  body_temp FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE health_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    heart_rate INT,
    temperature FLOAT,
    blood_pressure INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE health_data (
    user_id INT,
    heart_rate INT,
    blood_pressure VARCHAR(20),
    health_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id)
);

CREATE TABLE Stress_Data (
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    stress_level INT,
    device_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, timestamp)
);

CREATE TABLE User (
    user_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    location VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Health_Status (
    user_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    heart_rate INT,
    blood_pressure VARCHAR(20),
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, timestamp),
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES User(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Stress_Data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    stress_level INT,
    device_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE User_Profile (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    height FLOAT,
    weight FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Health_Data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    heart_rate INT,
    steps_count INT,
    calories_burned INT,
    distance_travelled FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Stress_Factors (
    user_id INT,
    stress_cause VARCHAR(100),
    stress_duration INT,
    mood_at_end VARCHAR(10),
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, stress_cause)
);
